{
  "message": "feat: enhance 'container already running' error with detailed info\n\nImproves user experience when trying to run a command with an existing container:\n\n- Show detailed container information (name, status, project, worktree, host path, original command)\n- Smart worktree flag detection - omit --worktree when current directory matches container's host path\n- Fix duplicate error messages by using SilenceErrors and SilenceUsage\n- Clean, readable error format with all relevant debugging information\n- Add comprehensive tests for label parsing and container details\n\nBefore:\n  Error: container already running for this worktree\n  [duplicate messages and command help]\n\nAfter:\n  container already running for this worktree\n\n  Container Details:\n    Name: packnplay-myproject-main\n    Status: Up 5 minutes\n    Project: myproject\n    Worktree: main\n    Host Path: /Users/jesse/myproject\n    Original Command: packnplay run --git-creds claude code\n\n  To run your command in the existing container:\n    packnplay run --reconnect bash\n\n  To stop the existing container:\n    packnplay stop\n\n\ud83e\udd16 Generated with Claude Code",
